# Optional: maps container, compose project, or Coolify resource names
# to friendly app keys used in B2 object filenames.
#
# Lives at /etc/backups/aliases.conf on the VPS. One per line:
#   <container-or-project-or-resource-name>=<short-key>
#
# You usually don't need this — auto-discovery uses Coolify's
# resourceName (with the trailing UUID stripped) or the compose project
# name, which is fine for most cases. Use this only if you want a
# specific filename like "achievement-tracker" instead of whatever the
# label happens to say.

# Examples:
# postgresql-database-abc123def456ghi789jkl0=achievement-tracker
# coolify-db=coolify
# bsky_postgres_1=bsky
